Token.Abstract: If the app delegate conforms to this protocol then the methods included will be called as appropriate.

Method called when the Bridge services return an error code that this version of the app is no longer supported. If not implemented or returns @NO then the BridgeNetworkManager will handle the error with a general message. In any case it will also pass the error through to the completion handler of the call that triggered the error. This method will only be called once per app launch.

ReturnValue.Abstract: @YES if the error has been handled by the delegate.

Token.Abstract: Method called when the Bridge services return an error code that the user has not consented. If not implemented or returns @NO then the BridgeNetworkManager will just log the error to the console. In any case it will also pass the error through to the completion handler of the call that triggered the error.

ReturnValue.Abstract: @YES if the error has been handled by the delegate.
